1. b3 { [%clk 0:02:30] } 1... d6 { [%clk 0:05:00] } 2. f3 { [%clk 0:02:29] } 2... e5 { [%clk 0:04:59] } 3. e4 { [%clk 0:02:28] } 3... Nc6 { [%clk 0:04:56] } 4. Bb5 { [%csl Ga7][%cal Gb5e8,Gg1a7] [%clk 0:02:24] } 4... Ne7 { [%clk 0:04:55] } 5. Qxa7 { [%clk 0:02:20] } 5... Kd8 { [%clk 0:04:47] } 6. Qa4 { [%clk 0:02:17] } 6... g5 { Exactly at this position, here i had an unusual idea of a tactical vision making use of kings position by setting up a mate threat and the clumsy coordination of rook in the back rank. So here what i visioned was: Ne3-d5 to force exchange, after Nd5 ed5 i expected Ne7 and then Bd7! with the threat of Qd7 mate and here comes the main idea: after Qd7 i thought about c6, trapping my bishop and preventing mate, but i can take dxc6 and if Kd8 cxb7 is with check and wins material. But if bxc6 bxc6 now my key move was Qa7! hitting b8 Rook and threatening d7 mate at the same time. And if Rb7 Qa8.. Similar position happened in the game, so i will show. } { [%csl Ga7,Gd7][%cal Gd1e3,Ge3d5] [%clk 0:04:43] } 7. Ne3 { [%clk 0:02:15] } 7... h5 { [%clk 0:04:42] } 8. Nd5 { [%clk 0:02:12] } 8... Nxd5 { [%clk 0:04:35] } 9. exd5 { [%clk 0:02:12] } 9... Ne7 { [%clk 0:04:27] } 10. Be8 { [%clk 0:01:34] } 10... Nc6 { [%clk 0:04:15] } (10... b5 11. Bxb5) (10... c6 11. dxc6 bxc6 (11... Kxe8 12. c7+) 12. Qa7! { So this is was original plan when i played Ne3. } { [%csl Gd7,Gb8][%cal Gb8b7,Ga7a8] }) 11. dxc6 { [%clk 0:01:30] } 11... b5 { [%clk 0:04:05] } 12. Qa7 { [%clk 0:01:29] } 12... Rc8 { [%clk 0:03:53] } 13. Bd7 { [%clk 0:01:27] } 13... Bxc6 { [%clk 0:03:50] } 14. Bxc6 { [%clk 0:01:24] } 14... g4 { [%clk 0:03:48] } 15. Nd3 { [%clk 0:01:21] } 15... gxf3 { [%clk 0:03:47] } 16. gxf3 { [%clk 0:01:19] } 16... Qg2 { [%clk 0:03:45] } 17. O-O-O { [%clk 0:01:18] } 17... Bh6 { [%clk 0:03:44] } 18. Nxe5 { [%clk 0:01:12] } 18... Bxd2+ { [%clk 0:03:42] } 19. Kb1 { [%csl Gg2,Gd2,Ga1][%cal Gf3f4,Gc6g2,Gd1d8] [%clk 0:01:11] } 19... dxe5 { [%clk 0:03:25] } 20. Bxe5 { [%csl Gf6,Gd8,Ge8][%cal Ge5f6] [%clk 0:01:09] } 20... Ke7 { [%clk 0:03:15] } 21. Qc5+ { 1-0 Black resigns. } { [%clk 0:01:05] } 1-0


