1. c3 { [%clk 0:02:30] } 1... d5 { [%clk 0:05:00] } 2. Ng3 { [%clk 0:02:30] } 2... c6 { [%csl Gg7] [%clk 0:04:58] } 3. Nh5 { well Nh5 looks like a dubious move or at least cheapo. But my idea was actually to force Be5 d4 and exchange minors or if Ne6, blacks pieces are placed badly. So only g6 can be played. I lose tempo, but weaken some squares. } { [%clk 0:02:26] } 3... g6 { [%clk 0:04:52] } 4. Ng7+ { Here i sacrificed my knight to ruin his castling rights. So i knew objectively this was not the best move, but who cares, its blitz. } { [%clk 0:02:14] } 4... Kd7 { [%clk 0:04:51] } 5. e4 { i could try to save my knight maybe with d4 or smt, but i wanted to open position asap while king is in the middle. } { [%csl Gd7,Gd5][%cal Ge4d5] [%clk 0:02:13] } 5... Be5 { [%clk 0:04:46] } 6. exd5 { [%clk 0:02:07] } 6... cxd5 { [%clk 0:04:39] } (6... Bxg7 7. dxc6+ { i believed there could be compensation or practical chances at least. }) 7. Qa4+ { [%clk 0:01:46] } 7... Kc7 { [%clk 0:04:36] } 8. Ne8+ { [%clk 0:01:45] } 8... Kb8 { [%clk 0:04:34] } 9. f4 { And the knight has been saved! This is a picturesque position of geometry. You cannot see everyday a knight on e8 in enemy camp dominating a bishop in the middle of the board on move 8th. } { [%csl Ge5,Gc7,Gd6,Gf6,Gg7,Ge8][%cal Ge5g7,Ge5c7] [%clk 0:01:40] } 9... Bc7 { [%clk 0:04:27] } 10. Nxc7 { [%clk 0:01:36] } 10... Qxc7 { [%clk 0:04:23] } 11. Bd4 { [%clk 0:01:32] } 11... f6 { [%clk 0:04:21] } 12. O-O { [%clk 0:01:29] } 12... Ne6 { [%clk 0:04:19] } 13. Be3 { [%clk 0:01:25] } 13... Bf7 { [%clk 0:04:17] } 14. Nb3 { [%clk 0:01:24] } 14... Nb6 { [%clk 0:04:16] } 15. Qb5 { [%clk 0:01:20] } 15... Rd8 { [%clk 0:04:08] } 16. f5 { [%clk 0:01:19] } 16... gxf5 { [%clk 0:04:03] } 17. Bxf5 { [%cal Gf5e6,Ge3f4] [%clk 0:01:19] } 17... Qc4 { [%clk 0:03:51] } 18. Qa5 { [%clk 0:01:10] } 18... Nc7 { [%clk 0:03:39] } 19. Nc5 { [%clk 0:00:49] } 19... e6 { [%clk 0:03:29] } 20. Bd3 { [%clk 0:00:47] } 20... Qh4 { [%clk 0:03:26] } 21. b4 { [%clk 0:00:32] } 21... Rg8 { [%clk 0:03:19] } 22. b5 { [%clk 0:00:31] } 22... e5 { [%clk 0:03:10] } 23. Na6+ { [%clk 0:00:27] } 23... Nxa6 { [%clk 0:03:03] } 24. bxa6 { [%clk 0:00:25] } 24... d4 { [%clk 0:02:56] } 25. cxd4 { [%clk 0:00:23] } 25... Bd5 { [%clk 0:02:55] } 26. Rf2 { [%clk 0:00:21] } 26... Qh3 { [%clk 0:02:50] } 27. Bf1 { [%clk 0:00:19] } 27... bxa6 { [%clk 0:02:36] } 28. dxe5 { [%clk 0:00:17] } 28... fxe5 { [%clk 0:02:32] } 29. Bxb6 { [%clk 0:00:16] } 29... axb6 { [%clk 0:02:20] } 30. Qxb6+ { [%clk 0:00:16] } 30... Bb7 { [%clk 0:02:13] } 31. Rb1 { [%clk 0:00:16] } 31... Ra7 { [%clk 0:02:08] } 32. Qd6+ { [%clk 0:00:13] } 32... Ka8 { [%clk 0:02:04] } 33. Rf8+ { [%clk 0:00:12] } 33... Rxf8 { [%clk 0:01:57] } 34. gxh3 { [%clk 0:00:11] } 34... Rg8+ { [%clk 0:01:53] } 35. Kf2 *


