1. b3 { [%clk 0:01:00] } 1... Ng6 { [%clk 0:01:00] } 2. c4 { [%clk 0:01:00] } 2... f6 { [%clk 0:01:00] } 3. d4 { [%clk 0:00:59] } 3... Nf7 { [%clk 0:01:00] } 4. g3 { [%clk 0:00:59] } 4... O-O { [%clk 0:00:58] } 5. d5 { [%clk 0:00:58] } 5... c6 { [%clk 0:00:57] } 6. Nfe3 { [%csl Gc4,Gd5,Ge3,Gh1,Gc6] [%clk 0:00:57] } 6... c5 { [%csl Ga1,Gb1,Gd5,Ga8] [%clk 0:00:57] } 7. Nf5 { [%clk 0:00:56] } 7... e6 { [%clk 0:00:56] } 8. Nh4 { to open the file! Here i took a risk with Nh4. I saw both the mating idea with Rg6 sac if he plays g6, but also the h2 will be free after the exchange on h4, which would force me to play Kf1. But in a bullet game, i believed g6 is more likely to be played than Qh2, so i took the psychological risk :) } { [%cal Gg1g8,Gb1h7,Ga1f6] [%clk 0:00:53] } 8... Nxh4 { [%clk 0:00:55] } 9. gxh4 { [%clk 0:00:53] } 9... g6 { [%clk 0:00:54] } 10. Rxg6+ { [%clk 0:00:51] } 10... Bg7 { [%clk 0:00:31] } (10... hxg6 11. Qxg6+ Bg7 12. Bxf6 { [%csl Gg7][%cal Gg6g7] }) 11. Bxf6 { [%clk 0:00:49] } 11... Qxh2 { [%clk 0:00:27] } 12. Rxg7+ { 1-0 Black resigns. } { [%cal Gg8h8,Gb1h7] [%clk 0:00:48] } 1-0


