[SetUp "1"]

{ Here, although black has a material advantage and a pressure on whites king, it also has a problem to deal with regarding his king safety and b7 pawn. Firstly, d5 with the idea of Be4 does not work due to Nb7+ Kc7 N3c5. Also taking on e5 is not an option as it is too dangerous. So black has two candidate moves: 0-0-0 and 0-0. But 0-0 -0 looks very dangerous as 3 pieces attack on c6. } { [%csl Gd8,Gb7] }
1... O-O!! { This solves two problems at once. Although the lack of g pawns, make it look dangerous for black king, but there is an usual safety due to current unavailability of g file for white, so it needs time, in which black can build a safety shelter with Bg6. b7 pawn is not relevant anymore in a position where every tempo counts. Now white has to deal with pressure on his king. } { [%csl Gh1,Gg1,Gg2,Gg8][%cal Gh7g6,Gh6h5] } 2. Qf3 dxe5 { [%cal Gh8a1,Gh7b1] } 3. dxe5 Bxe5+ 4. Rxe5 Qxe5+ 5. Bd4 Qf5 6. Rg1+ Bg6 0-1


