[UTCTime "11:44:05"]

{ Always 3 squares. So it might look like it doesnt make any direct difference how rook is placed in terms of control. But for other pieces it differs. So it indirectly effects by being placed where it is placed, which means other piece cannot be placed there. As we have seen, all other pieces in the corner control minimum squares except rook as rooks are indifferent. So placing rooks on a1 and h1 makes difference for other pieces and therefore for the whole. In short, rooks placed in corners are efficient for the whole. } { [%cal Ga1a4,Gb1b4,Gc1c4,Gd1d4,Ge1e4,Gf1f4,Gg1g4,Gh1h4,Gb5h5,Gg5a5] }
 *


