{ Here the imperial king has started his brave march to the middle of the battlefield! }
11... Ke6 12. Nc7+ Kxe5 { This spectacular position is according to engine is 0.00!! Despite blacks king being right in the centre (no this is not KoTH game), white has no way to exploit. Going into this line, i've felt my king is astonishingly safe on e5! } 13. Kc1 (13. f4+ Kf6 14. Nd5+ Ke6 { [%cal Ge6d7] } 15. e4 (15. Rxa1 Kd7 16. Kc2 e6 17. Nc3 g5 { dark squares are too weak. } { [%csl Gd4] }) 15... Kd7 { [%cal Gg7g5] }) 13... g5 { [%csl Gf4,Gd4] } 14. h4 Qg6 { [%csl Gc2][%cal Gg6c2] } 15. e4 g4 { [%cal Gf8h6] } 16. Bd3 Bh6+ 17. Kb1 g3? 18. Kxa1 e6 { [%cal Ge5f6,Gf6e7] } 19. h5 Qg7 { king-queen battery :) } { [%cal Gg7a1] } 20. Kb1 Kf6 21. fxg3 { the reason why black is better in this position and all the crazy king march has worked without any real danger was due to lack of dark-squared bishop for white. White's light squared bishop is hitting the pawn wall and won't be able to encounter any danger created by blacks bishop and queen on dark squares. } { [%csl Gd3,Gc4,Gb3,Ga2,Ge4] } 21... Ke7 22. Qe1 Qe5 { centralising the queen and prepping the deadly battery on dark squares. } { [%cal Gh6g7] } 23. Nb5 Nxb5 24. cxb5 Bg7 { 0-1 White resigns. } 0-1


