{ [#] Chess 960-Position 310 Blitz, 3+2 } { This blitz game (along with another one) was played over the board in Prague when the Prague International Chess Festival 2022 came to the end. }
1. e4 b5 2. d3 c5 3. b3 Nc6 4. g3 d6 5. f4 Nd7 6. Nfe3 O-O 7. O-O e6 8. Qd2 b4 9. Nf2 Nd4 10. f5 Ne5 11. Nfg4 Nxg4 12. Nxg4 exf5 13. exf5 Bxh1 14. Qg5! { White is threatening two mates in one. } 14... Re8 { I do not remember exactly when did I
check on f6. (I was already short of time.) } 15. Bxd4 Qc6!? { A surprising move and a good practical chance. } 16. Nf6+ (16. Rf2 cxd4 17. Nf6+ Kf8 18. Nxh7+ Kg8 19. Qh5! f6 20. Qg6 Rf8 21. g4 $18 (21. Re1 $18)) 16... Kf8 17. Nxh7+ Kg8 18. Nf6+ Kf8 19. Nh7+ Kg8 20. Nf6+ Kf8 21. Nd7+ Kg8 (21... Qxd7 22. Bxg7+ Bxg7 23. f6) 22. Rf2 cxd4 23. Nf6+ Kf8 24. Nh7+ Kg8 25. Nf6+ { 1/2-1/2 The game is a draw. } (25. Qh5! f6 26. Qg6 Rf8 27. g4 Rbe8 (27... Bd5 28. Re1! { Black can play neither 28...Bf7? 29.Nxf6#, nor 28...Rbe8 29.Rxe8, 30.Nxf6+. White has a decisive attack, as there is no defence against 29.g5, after which black cannot even bring his queen to f7. }) 28. g5 Bd5 29. Qh5 $18) 1/2-1/2


