[ChapterName "GM AnishOnYoutube - Tasshaq"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/RDtcPDNu/WMeGnpWy"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/Tasshaq"]
[FEN "RNBKQBNR/PPPPPPPP/8/8/8/8/pppppppp/rnbkqbnr w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]

1. Nh6 { [%csl Ge3][%cal Gh6f5,Gf5e3,Gb1c3,Gc3d5,Gd5e3] [%clk 0:03:00] } 1... Nc3 { [%clk 0:03:00] } 2. Nf5 { [%clk 0:02:59] } 2... Nd5 { [%csl Ge3] [%clk 0:02:59] } 3. g8=Q { [%clk 0:02:59] } 3... Nh3 { [%csl Gf4,Gg1][%cal Gh3f4,Gd5f4,Gg2g1] [%clk 0:02:54] } 4. Bh6 { [%clk 0:02:58] } 4... g1=Q { [%clk 0:02:52] } 5. f8=Q { [%clk 0:02:57] } 5... Bg2 { [%csl Gf1,Gd5][%cal Gf2f1,Gg2d5] [%clk 0:02:51] } 6. Qxd5 { [%clk 0:02:57] } 6... f1=Q { [%csl Ge3][%cal Gg1e3,Gf5e3] [%clk 0:02:49] } 7. Qd3 { [%clk 0:02:56] } 7... b1=Q { [%clk 0:02:46] } 8. Qh5 { [%clk 0:02:55] } 8... Nf4 { when i played this i was hoping for an exchange on f4 so that my queen is on the diagonal h2-b8 and putting pressure on c7. } { [%clk 0:02:43] } 9. Bxf4 { [%clk 0:02:53] } 9... Qxf4 { [%clk 0:02:43] } 10. e8=Q { [%clk 0:02:46] } 10... Qxc7+ { [%csl Gc7,Gb6,Gb1][%cal Gd8c7,Gg1b6,Gb1b6] [%clk 0:02:41] } 11. Ke7 { [%clk 0:02:37] } 11... Qgc5+ { [%clk 0:02:27] } 12. Nd6 { [%clk 0:02:21] } (12. Kf7 { to this i was planning Bd5 and Bb2 followed by Rg1 and there should be mate somewhere for sure. } { [%csl Gd5][%cal Gg2d5,Gc1b2,Gb2g7,Gh1g1,Ge1f1] }) 12... Q5xd6+ { [%clk 0:02:20] } 13. Qxd6 { [%clk 0:02:18] } 13... Qxd6+ { [%clk 0:02:20] } 14. Kxd6 { In his stream, he was looking for Qg3, which was also good. } { [%csl Gg3][%cal Ge1g3] [%clk 0:02:18] } 14... Ba3+ { But i wanted to include more pieces in the attack by making c1.Q also possible and promoting with check after Kc7. } { [%clk 0:02:18] } (14... Qg3+) 15. Kc7 { [%clk 0:02:13] } 15... c1=Q+ { 0-1 White resigns. } { [%cal Gb8c6,Gc1c6] [%clk 0:02:13] } 16. Nc6 (16. Kd8 Qb6#) 16... Qxc6+ 17. Kb8 (17. Kd8 Qcb6#) 17... Qd6+ 18. Qxd6 Bxd6# 0-1


[Event "Casual Standard game"]
[Site "https://lichess.org/Y0qQSDrS"]
[Date "2020.10.21"]
[White "Game-Changer20"]
[Black "Tasshaq"]
[Result "0-1"]
[WhiteElo "1772"]
[BlackElo "2402"]
[TimeControl "180+0"]
[Termination "Normal"]
[Variant "From Position"]
[ECO "?"]
[Opening "?"]
[StudyName "Cute Upside down game collection"]
[ChapterName "Game-Changer20 - Tasshaq"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/RDtcPDNu/Nmmgpwg4"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/Tasshaq"]
[FEN "RNBKQBNR/PPPPPPPP/8/8/8/8/pppppppp/rnbkqbnr w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ first upside down game i have ever played and thanks to this game i discovered the concept of smothered mate. }
1. Nf6 { [%clk 0:03:00] } 1... Nc3 { [%clk 0:03:00] } 2. Ng4 { I almost fell for the mate here and it took me some time to adjust myself. } { [%csl Ge3] [%clk 0:02:54] } 2... Nd5 { [%clk 0:02:45] } 3. g8=Q { [%clk 0:02:48] } 3... Nf3 { So i thought knights are very powerful in such dynamics, therefore should be developed and wanted to play Nd4 to create same threat as she did to me. } { [%csl Gd4,Ge6,Gc6][%cal Gf3d4] [%clk 0:02:39] } 4. Nc6 { [%clk 0:02:37] } 4... g1=Q { [%clk 0:02:29] } 5. Nb4 { Tries to distract my knight. } { [%cal Gd5b4,Gg4e3] [%clk 0:02:26] } 5... Nd4 { Best defence is to attack! Every tempo counts. } { [%csl Ge6,Gc6] [%clk 0:02:22] } 6. Qg6 { [%clk 0:02:14] } 6... Qxg4 { Getting rid of g4 knight, which was threatening mate, now frees my d5 knight. } { [%clk 0:02:20] } 7. Qxg4 { [%clk 0:02:10] } 7... Nxb4 { 0-1 White resigns. } { Beautiful picture showing the hopelessness of the lone queen against the powerful knight combo. } { [%csl Gc6,Ge6,Gg4,Gd4,Gb4] [%clk 0:02:20] } 0-1


