1. Nf6 { [%clk 0:01:30] } 1... Nc3 { [%clk 0:03:00] } 2. Ng4 { [%clk 0:01:29] } 2... Nd5 { [%clk 0:02:58] } 3. g8=Q { [%clk 0:01:29] } 3... b1=Q { Black has to be very careful. playing moves like b1. promotion lets white attack the knight very quickly, which can only be protected by a queen which cannot control important mating squares like knights do: e3 and c3. } { [%csl Gd5][%cal Gg8g5,Gg5d5] [%clk 0:02:56] } 4. Qg5 { [%clk 0:01:28] } 4... Qb3 { [%clk 0:02:49] } 5. Qxd5 { [%csl Gd5,Ge3,Gc3][%cal Gb3d5,Gg4e3] [%clk 0:01:26] } 5... Qg3 { [%clk 0:02:42] } 6. Qe4 { [%csl Ge3,Gg4][%cal Gg4e3] [%clk 0:01:20] } 6... Ba3 { [%clk 0:02:31] } 7. Ne3+ { [%clk 0:01:16] } 7... Qxe3 { [%clk 0:02:25] } 8. Qxe3 { [%clk 0:01:16] } 8... c1=Q { [%csl Gb3,Gc2] [%clk 0:02:22] } 9. Qb3+ { [%clk 0:01:12] } 9... Qc2 { [%clk 0:02:18] } 10. Qxc2+ { [%clk 0:01:12] } (10. Qxa3 { was also possible but not as strong as the move in the game, exchanging queen and dragging king out of safety is more important than the material at this stage. }) 10... Kxc2 { [%clk 0:02:17] } 11. Bg7 { [%clk 0:01:10] } 11... Rb1 { [%clk 0:02:11] } 12. f8=Q { [%clk 0:01:09] } 12... Kd1 { [%clk 0:02:09] } 13. Qf4 { [%clk 0:01:06] } 13... a1=Q { [%clk 0:01:59] } 14. Qa4+ { Usually, a knight is there to block the check, but this time bishop is doing terrible job, not only incapable of blocking the check, but also making queen on a1 incapable by blocking it. It is one of these cases, its absence is better than its presence. } { [%csl Ga3,Ga4][%cal Ga3c2,Ga1a4] [%clk 0:01:05] } 14... Kc1 { [%clk 0:01:53] } 15. Bxa1 { [%clk 0:01:01] } 15... Rxa1 { [%clk 0:01:51] } 16. Qc4+ { [%clk 0:01:00] } 16... Kd1 { [%clk 0:01:49] } 17. Qb3+ { [%clk 0:00:57] } 17... Kc1 { [%clk 0:01:46] } 18. Qg6 { [%csl Gc2] [%clk 0:00:57] } 18... Qd1 { [%clk 0:01:36] } (18... d1=Q 19. Qc6+ { [%csl Gc2][%cal Gc6c2] }) 19. Qc6+ { [%clk 0:00:55] } 19... Qc2 { [%clk 0:01:32] } 20. Qcxc2# { 1-0 White wins by checkmate. } { [%clk 0:00:55] } 1-0


