1. Nh6 { [%clk 0:03:00] } 1... Nc3 { [%clk 0:01:30] } 2. Nf5 { [%clk 0:03:00] } 2... Nd5 { [%clk 0:01:29] } 3. g8=Q { [%clk 0:02:59] } 3... b1=Q { [%clk 0:01:28] } 4. Bh6 { [%clk 0:02:58] } 4... Ba3 { making a room for king also promotion possibilities. } { [%csl Gd1,Gc1] [%clk 0:01:26] } 5. f8=Q { [%clk 0:02:57] } 5... Nxc7 { Trying to trick my opponent with this unexpected knight sacrifice. It is to bring king out of its shell. } { [%clk 0:01:18] } 6. Kxc7 { [%clk 0:02:53] } (6. Ne3+ Kc1 7. Kxc7 { the intermediate check was necessary in order to block c pawns promotion with check after Kxc7. But i was hoping that my opponent misses this subtlety during the game. To see an example of a game with Ne3, simply check the next game. } { [%csl Gc2][%cal Gc2c1] }) 6... c1=Q+ { [%clk 0:01:18] } 7. Nc6 { [%clk 0:02:53] } 7... Qxc6+ { eliminating all the shelters of the king. } { [%clk 0:01:13] } 8. Kxc6 { [%clk 0:02:49] } 8... Qc1+ { not letting king back to home. } { [%csl Gd8,Gc7,Gb8][%cal Gc6c7] [%clk 0:01:12] } 9. Kb6 { [%clk 0:02:48] } 9... Rb1+ { [%clk 0:01:11] } 10. Ka6 { [%clk 0:02:46] } 10... Qc6+ { 0-1 White resigns. } { [%csl Gb5][%cal Ga6a5,Gc6b5] [%clk 0:01:07] } 0-1


