1. Nf6 { [%clk 0:01:30] } 1... Na3?? { Elementary concept of Upside Down Chess. } { [%cal Gf6d5,Gd5c3,Gd5e3] [%clk 0:03:00] } 2. Nd5 { 1-0 Black resigns. } { And mate on next move is inevitable! This is probably the earliest unavoidability case that is ever possible in any chess (reasonable) starting positions at all. (Im not counting a starting position construction in which simply there is no mate after whites first move because it has not "game" element in it. But in upside chess a game is possible if correctly played and can last longer than 2 moves) } { [%csl Gc3,Ge3,Gd1][%cal Gd5c3,Gd5e3] [%clk 0:01:25] } 1-0


