1. Nh6 { [%clk 0:03:00] } 1... Nc3 { [%clk 0:01:30] } 2. Ng4 { [%clk 0:02:59] } 2... Nd5 { [%clk 0:01:30] } 3. g8=Q { [%clk 0:02:57] } 3... b1=Q { [%clk 0:01:28] } 4. Bh6 { [%clk 0:02:56] } 4... Ba3 { so while the knight is already on d5, i thought why not develop a piece with the pressure on d2 and which creates me options of promoting c1.Q or Kc1 in case of mate danger. A multipurpose move. } { [%csl Ge7][%cal Gc2c1,Gd1c1] [%clk 0:01:25] } 5. f8=Q { [%clk 0:02:54] } 5... Bxe7+ { [%clk 0:01:24] } 6. Qexe7 { [%clk 0:02:51] } 6... Nxe7 { [%clk 0:01:24] } 7. Ne3+ { [%clk 0:02:49] } 7... Kc1 { [%clk 0:01:23] } 8. Qxe7 { [%csl Gb2,Ga3][%cal Gb1b2] [%clk 0:02:45] } 8... Nf3 { Wrong move due to attack on dark squares. } { [%csl Ga3,Gb2][%cal Gg2g1,Gf3d4] [%clk 0:01:12] } 9. Qa3+ { [%clk 0:02:35] } 9... Qb2 { [%clk 0:01:11] } 10. Bf8 { [%clk 0:02:30] } (10. Qgb3 { would win on the stop as it is creating a double threat of Qxc2 and Qxb2 which cannot be defended at the same time. } { [%csl Gc2,Gb2] } 10... Rb1 (10... Qd1 11. Qaxb2#) 11. Qxc2#) 10... Rb1 { [%clk 0:01:03] } 11. Qgb3 { [%clk 0:02:21] } 11... d1=Q { now black is in time to protect c2. } { [%csl Gc2][%cal Gb1b2,Gd1c2] [%clk 0:00:52] } 12. Qaxb2+ { [%clk 0:02:15] } 12... Rxb2 { [%clk 0:00:50] } 13. Ba3 { [%clk 0:02:14] } 13... a1=Q { [%csl Gb2][%cal Ga1b2] [%clk 0:00:49] } 14. Bxb2+ { [%clk 0:02:10] } 14... Qxb2 { [%clk 0:00:49] } 15. Qxb2+ { [%clk 0:02:09] } 15... Kxb2 { this suddenly leaves white with an unsafe king as black has two and potentially 3 queens on the board at the moment. } { [%csl Ge7,Gf6][%cal Gg2g1,Gg1g5] [%clk 0:00:49] } 16. Nxd1+ { [%clk 0:02:08] } 16... exd1=Q { [%csl Gh8,Ge1,Gd1,Gf3] [%clk 0:00:48] } 17. Re8 { [%clk 0:02:06] } 17... Ng5 { [%csl Gf7][%cal Gg5f7] [%clk 0:00:42] } 18. h8=Q+ { [%clk 0:02:05] } 18... Kb1 { [%clk 0:00:39] } 19. Rxe1 { [%clk 0:02:00] } 19... fxe1=Q { [%csl Gf7][%cal Gg5f7] [%clk 0:00:39] } 20. Qf6 { [%clk 0:01:56] } 20... Qf3 { [%clk 0:00:33] } (20... Qd4 21. Qxd4 Nf7#) 21. Qb6+ { [%clk 0:01:52] } (21. Qxf3 Nxf3 { [%csl Gg5][%cal Gg2g1,Gg2g5] }) 21... Kc1 { [%csl Gf8][%cal Gf3f8] [%clk 0:00:30] } 22. Nc6 { [%clk 0:01:46] } 22... Qf8# { 0-1 Black wins by checkmate. } { [%clk 0:00:28] } 0-1


