[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/Tasshaq"]
[FEN "R7/P4p2/5kp1/3p3p/8/r3P2P/5PPK/8 b - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ Here Black could try with h4. But Carlsen showed in the press-conference the following winning plan for white, if h4 was played. The actual game continuation ended in resignation by Anand for the similar winning plan of the white. } { [%cal Gh5h4] }
1... h4 2. g4 hxg3+ { Here it is important not to capture with King, because black can exchange d pawn for e pawn after which black can draw with putting King on h7-g7. } { [%csl Gg7,Gh7][%cal Gh2g3,Ga3g3,Gd5d4,Gf6g7] } 3. fxg3 Ra2+ 4. Kg1 Ra3 5. Kf2 { Black plays waiting moves as Carlsen noted that Blacks moves dont matter. } 5... Ra2+ 6. Ke1 Ra3 7. Ke2 Ra2+ 8. Kd3 Ra4 9. Kc3 Ra1 10. Kb2 Ra4 11. Kb3 Ra1 12. Kb4 Kg7 13. Kc5 { Here no Ra5 because of Kb6. } 13... Ra3 14. Kxd5 Ra1 15. h4 Ra3 16. e4 Ra1 17. e5 Ra3 18. g4 Ra1 { [%csl Gh4,Gg4,Gg6][%cal Gh4h8] } 19. h5 gxh5 20. gxh5 Ra3 21. h6+ Kh7 { [%csl Gf7,Gf6][%cal Gd5e4,Ge4f5,Gf5f6] } 22. Ke4 { [%csl Gg7,Gh7][%cal Gh6g7] } 22... Ra1 23. Kf5 Ra6 { [%csl Gf6,Gf7][%cal Gf5g5,Gg5f4,Gf4f5,Ga6f6,Gf5f7] } 24. Kg5 Rg6+ 25. Kf4 Ra6 26. Kf5 { Black has to let King on f6 now and White wins then f7 pawn. } { [%csl Gf6] } *


