which follow that Nimzowitsch was also capable of constructing
fantastic blockading possibilities for his knights over the
board. } 1... Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Nf3 Bxc3+ 5. bxc3 d6 6. Qc2 Qe7 7. Ba3 c5 8. g3 b6 9. Bg2 Bb7 10. O-O O-O 11. Nh4 Bxg2 12. Kxg2 { ? } 12... Qb7+ { ! } 13. Kg1 Qa6 14. Qb3 Nc6 15. Rfd1 Na5 16. Qb5 Qxb5 17. cxb5 Nc4 18. Bc1 a6 19. bxa6 Rxa6 20. dxc5 bxc5 21. Ng2 Nd5 22. Rd3 Rfa8 { Black's blockading
knights, firmly established on light squares, create an
impression both of power and of pictorial beauty. The same
could also be said of Mannheimer-Nimzowitsch 1930. } 23. e4 Ne5 { 0-1 White resigns. } 0-1


