[Event "Steinitz - Zukertort World Championship Match"]
[Site "New York, NY USA"]
[Date "1886.01.20"]
[Round "5"]
[White "Johannes Zukertort"]
[Black "Wilhelm Steinitz"]
[Result "1-0"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/reallynotbatman"]
[Variant "Standard"]
[ECO "D10"]
[Opening "Slav Defense"]
[StudyName "W. Steinitz, WcH Selected Games"]
[ChapterName "Johannes Zukertort - Wilhelm Steinitz"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/5OdXI9BB/SVuvavwe"]

1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 { The slav defence } 3. Nc3 Nf6 (3... Bf5? 4. cxd5 cxd5 5. Qb3 { Attacking the b- and the d-pawn } 5... b6 6. e4 dxe4 7. Bb5+ Nd7 8. f3 exf3 9. Nxf3 Nf6 10. Ne5) (3... dxc4 4. e4 b5 5. a4 b4 6. Na2 Nf6 7. e5 Nd5 8. Bxc4) 4. e3 Bf5 { This move allows white to gain a tempo, as seen in the game. More popular moves are: } (4... e6 5. Nf3 { The semi-slav }) (4... a6 5. Nf3 b5 6. b3 { The chameleon variation }) 5. cxd5 cxd5 6. Qb3 { Attacking the b- and the d--pawn } 6... Bc8 { Black can sacrifice the b-pawn } (6... Nc6 7. Qxb7 Bd7 8. Qb3 Rb8 9. Qd1 e5 10. dxe5 Nxe5) (6... Qd7?! 7. Nf3 e6 8. Bb5 Nc6 9. Ne5 Qc7 10. Qa4 Rc8 11. Qxa7 Bd6 12. Nxc6 bxc6 13. Qxc7 Rxc7 14. Be2) 7. Nf3 Nc6 8. Ne5 e6 (8... Nxe5? 9. dxe5 Ne4 10. Nxd5 $16) 9. Bb5 (9. f4 Be7 10. Bd3 O-O 11. O-O) 9... Qc7 (9... Qb6) (9... Bd7 10. f4 Qb6) 10. Bd2 Bd6 11. f4 O-O 12. Rc1 Bxe5 { A mistake. Black loses his strong bishop and opens the f-file for white } (12... a6 13. Bd3 Na5 14. Qc2 b5 { [%cal Gg2g4] }) 13. fxe5 Ne8 (13... Ng4 14. h3 Nh6 15. O-O Bd7 16. Bd3) (13... Nd7 14. Bxc6 bxc6 15. Nb5 Qd8 16. Nd6 { White can establish his knight on d6, but black can develop the weak light squared bishop to a6 and attack the center with f6 } 16... f6 17. O-O Ba6 18. Rfe1 fxe5) 14. O-O f6 15. Bd3 Rf7 (15... Bd7 16. Nxd5 exd5 17. Qxd5+ Kh8 18. e6 Bc8 19. Qh5 g6 20. Qh6 Qg7 21. Qxg7+ Kxg7 22. d5 Ne5 (22... Bxe6 23. dxe6) 23. Bb5 { The center pawns give white strong compensation for the piece }) 16. Qc2 f5 { This is the only way to stop whites queen and bishop } (16... g6? 17. Bxg6 hxg6 18. Qxg6+ Ng7 (18... Kf8 19. e4) 19. exf6 { White is winning }) 17. Ne2 Bd7 { Cutting of the queen } (17... Qe7 18. g4 Qg5) 18. Rf2 { White can simply play g4 } (18. g4 fxg4?? (18... g6 19. gxf5 exf5 20. Nf4) 19. Bxh7+) 18... Rc8 19. Bc3 { White want to double the rooks, but: } (19. Rcf1 Qb6 20. Qb1 Nb4 21. Bxb4 Qxb4) 19... Qb6 20. Qd2 Ne7 21. Rcf1 Bb5 22. Bb1 Qa6 23. g4 g6 24. h3 Rc7 { A weak move. } (24... Bc4 25. a3 (25. b3? Bxe2 26. Rxe2 Rxc3 27. Qxc3 Qxe2) 25... Ng7) 25. Re1 { Unpinning the knight } 25... Ng7 (25... Bxe2 26. Rexe2 Nc6 27. gxf5 gxf5 28. Rg2+ Rg7 29. a3) 26. Nf4 Nc8 { This loses. Black could try: } (26... g5) 27. gxf5 gxf5 (27... Nxf5? 28. e4 dxe4 29. Bxe4 { Black can't stop the deadly d-pawn } 29... Rcd7 30. d5 exd5 (30... Ng7 31. d6 Bc6 32. Bxc6 Qxc6) 31. Bxf5 Rxf5 32. e6 Re7 33. Qd4) 28. Rg2 Kh8 29. Kh2 Qc6 30. Reg1 Ne7 31. Qf2 Qe8 { Steinitz used 24 minutes on this move. But the game is already lost } 32. Rxg7 { 1-0 Black resigns. } { The game would continue like this: } 32... Rxg7 33. Rxg7 Kxg7 34. Nxe6+ Kh8 35. Nxc7 { 1-0 Black resigns. } 1-0


[Event "Steinitz - Zukertort World Championship Match"]
[Site "St. Louis, MO USA"]
[Date "1886.02.03"]
[Round "6"]
[White "Wilhelm Steinitz"]
[Black "Johannes Zukertort"]
[Result "1-0"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/reallynotbatman"]
[Variant "Standard"]
[ECO "C67"]
[Opening "Ruy Lopez: Berlin Defense, Rio Gambit Accepted"]
[StudyName "W. Steinitz, WcH Selected Games"]
[ChapterName "Wilhelm Steinitz - Johannes Zukertort"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/5OdXI9BB/ko32UocR"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nf6 { Again the berlin defence } 4. O-O Nxe4 5. Re1 (5. d4 Nd6 6. Bxc6 dxc6 7. dxe5 Nf5 8. Qxd8+ Kxd8 9. Nc3) 5... Nd6 6. Nxe5 Nxe5 7. Rxe5+ Be7 8. Nc3 O-O (8... Nxb5? 9. Nd5! O-O 10. Nxe7+ Kh8 11. Qh5 { White is winning } 11... d6 12. Qxh7+ Kxh7 13. Rh5#) 9. Bd3 Bf6 10. Re3 g6 { Black has to defend against Bxh7+: } (10... a6?? 11. Bxh7+ Kxh7 12. Qh5+ Kg8 13. Rh3 { And black can resign }) (10... h6 11. Nd5) 11. b3 Re8 { Black should develop his light squared bishop } (11... b6 12. Bb2 Bb7 13. Qg4 Re8) 12. Qf3 Bg5 { The bishop was better on the a1-h8 diagonal } (12... Rxe3 13. fxe3 (13. Qxe3 b6) 13... Ne8 14. Ba3 d5) 13. Rxe8+ { White can sacrifice the exchange: } (13. Ba3 Bxe3 14. fxe3 { Black can't develop } 14... Re6 15. Rf1 f6 (15... Qe8? 16. Nd5) 16. Nd5) 13... Nxe8 14. Bb2 c6 (14... Bxd2? 15. Bc4 Nd6 (15... Qe7 16. Nd5 Qf8 17. Nf6+ { Mate in 4 }) 16. Ne4 Nxc4 17. bxc4 Bg5 18. Nxg5 Qxg5 19. Re1 Qd8 20. Bf6 Qf8 { White is winning }) 15. Ne4 Be7 16. Qe3 d5 17. Qd4 { This forces black to move the f-pawn, creating a weakness } 17... f6 18. Ng3 Be6 (18... c5 19. Qe3 { [%csl Gc8] } 19... Nc7 20. Re1 Be6 21. h4) 19. Re1 Ng7 20. h4 Qd7 21. h5 Bf7 22. hxg6 Bxg6 (22... hxg6 23. Ne4 Nh5) 23. Qe3 (23. Qf4 Rf8) 23... Kf7 24. Qf4 Re8 (24... Bxd3? 25. cxd3 Rf8 (25... Re8)) 25. Re3 Ne6 { This is a mistake, better is: } (25... Bd8 26. Qh4 Rxe3 27. fxe3 Qe6) 26. Qg4 Nf8 27. Nf5 Bc5 (27... Bd8? 28. Nh6+ Kg7 29. Bf5 Qd6 30. Rxe8 { White wins }) 28. Nh6+ Kg7 29. Nf5+ Kf7 30. Nh6+ { Always repeat } 30... Kg7 31. Nf5+ { Note that this match was not played with the threefold repetition rule. } 31... Kf7 32. Nh6+ Kg7 33. Nf5+ Kf7 34. Nh6+ Kg7 35. Bxg6 (35. Qh4 d4 36. Ng4 { White is winning }) 35... Qxg4 36. Nxg4 Rxe3 37. fxe3 Kxg6 38. Nxf6 { White wins a pawn } 38... Bb4 39. d3 Ne6 40. Kf2 h5 41. g4 h4 { Taking the pawn is stronger: } (41... hxg4 42. Nxg4 { White has no passed pawn and black can fight for a draw }) 42. Nh5 Bd6 43. Kg2 c5 44. Bf6 Ng5 45. Bxg5 Kxg5 46. Kh3 Be5 47. Nf4 (47. a4?? d4 48. e4 a5 { White is in Zugzwang, black wins }) 47... d4 (47... Bxf4? 48. exf4+ Kxf4 49. Kxh4 Ke5 50. g5 Ke6 51. Kh5 Kf7 52. Kh6 Kg8 53. Kg6 { White wins }) 48. Ne6+ Kf6 49. exd4 cxd4 50. Nc5 Kg5 (50... b6 51. Nd7+ Ke6 52. Nxe5 Kxe5 53. g5) 51. Nxb7 Kf4 52. Na5 Bf6 53. Nc6 Ke3 54. Nxa7 Kd2 55. Nc6 Kxc2 56. a4 Kxd3 57. Nb4+ Ke2 58. a5 Be7 59. Nd5 Kf3 (59... Bc5 60. a6 d3 61. Nc3+ Ke1 62. Ne4 d2 63. Nxd2 Kxd2 64. b4 Ba7 65. b5 Kd3 66. g5 { Blacks bishop can't stop all three pawns. }) 60. Nxe7 d3 61. Nd5 { 1-0 Black resigns. } 1-0


