1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 { The queens gambit declined } 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. Nf3 (4. cxd5 exd5 5. Bg5 Be7 6. e3 c6 7. Qc2) 4... dxc4 { The vienna variation } 5. e3 { e4 is the main alternative } (5. e4 Bb4 6. Bg5 c5 7. Bxc4 cxd4 8. Nxd4 Bxc3+ 9. bxc3 Qa5 10. Bb5+ Bd7 11. Bxf6 gxf6 12. Bxd7+ Nxd7 13. O-O a6) 5... c5 6. Bxc4 cxd4 { more common is : } (6... a6 7. O-O b5 8. Bb3 Bb7 9. Qe2 Nbd7 10. Rd1) 7. exd4 { White has an isolated d-pawn, similar to Game 7 } (7. Nxd4 a6 8. a4 Bd6 9. b3 O-O 10. O-O Bd7) 7... Be7 8. O-O O-O 9. Qe2 { White wants to play Rd1 } 9... Nbd7 (9... Nc6 10. Rd1 Na5 11. Bd3 b6 12. Bg5 Bb7 13. Rac1 Rc8) 10. Bb3 { This retreat is not necessary and the bishop might be better placed at d3 } (10. Rd1 Nb6 11. Bb3 (11. Bd3)) 10... Nb6 11. Bf4 Nbd5 12. Bg3 Qa5 13. Rac1 (13. Nxd5 Nxd5 14. Ne5 { Black can't develop his light squared bishop immediatly } 14... b6?? 15. Nc6 Qa6 16. Qxa6 Bxa6 17. Bxd5 exd5 18. Nxe7+) 13... Bd7 14. Ne5 Rfd8 15. Qf3 { This seems more natural } (15. f4) 15... Be8 16. Rfe1 Rac8 17. Bh4 Nxc3 18. bxc3 Qc7 19. Qd3 Nd5 20. Bxe7 { Trading of blacks good bishop } (20. Bg3 { Threatening a discovered attack on the queen } 20... Qa5 21. c4 Nf6 { With equality }) 20... Qxe7 21. Bxd5 { This trade favours black, better is: } (21. c4 Nf4 22. Qe3 Qf6 (22... Qg5 23. g3 Nh3+ 24. Kg2 Qxe3 (24... f6 25. Nf3 Qxe3 26. fxe3 Ng5 27. Nxg5 fxg5) 25. Rxe3 Ng5 26. h4 f6 27. hxg5 fxe5 28. Rxe5 Rxd4 29. Rxe6) 23. g3 Ng6 24. f4 { White is slightly better }) 21... Rxd5 22. c4 Rdd8 { The best move, since after Ra5 } (22... Ra5 23. d5 exd5? 24. Ng6) 23. Re3 Qd6 24. Rd1 f6 25. Rh3 h6 { Black should not accept the sacrifice: } (25... fxe5 26. Qxh7+ Kf8 27. Qh8+ Ke7 28. Qxg7+ Bf7 29. Qg5+ Kd7 30. d5) 26. Ng4 Qf4 27. Ne3 Ba4 28. Rf3 { Rd2 is better } (28. Rd2 b5 29. g3 (29. cxb5?? Rc1+ 30. Nf1 Bxb5 31. Qxb5 Qxd2) 29... Qg5 30. f4) 28... Qd6 29. Rd2 Bc6 30. Rg3 { White might try to force a perpetual check with Rxf6 } (30. Rxf6?! gxf6 31. Qg6+ Kf8 32. Qxf6+ (32. Qxh6+ Ke8 33. d5) 32... Ke8 33. Nf5 exf5 34. Re2+ Be4 35. Qxf5 Rd7 36. Rxe4+ Kd8) (30. d5 exd5 (30... Be8) 31. Nf5 Qc7) 30... f5 { Threat is f4 forking knight and rook } 31. Rg6 Be4 32. Qb3 Kh7 { Very important move, now white can never play Qxe6+ } (32... a6 33. c5 Rxc5 34. dxc5 Qxd2 35. Qxe6+ Kh8 36. Rxh6+) 33. c5 (33. Rg3 f4 { Black wins }) 33... Rxc5 (33... Qc6?? 34. Rxe6) 34. Rxe6 Rc1+ 35. Nd1 { Nf1 is slightly stronger } (35. Nf1 Qf4 36. Qe3 Qxe3 37. fxe3 Bd5 38. Re5 f4 39. exf4 (39. Rf2 fxe3 40. Rxe3 Bc4) 39... Bc4) 35... Qf4 36. Qb2 (36. Qe3 Qxe3 37. fxe3 Bc2 { Black wins }) 36... Rb1 37. Qc3 Rc8 { A deflection } 38. Rxe4 (38. Qxc8 Qxd2) 38... Qxe4 { 0-1 White resigns. } 0-1


