1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nf6 4. d3 { This is commonly used to avoid the berlin endgame } 4... d6 (4... Bc5 5. c3 O-O 6. O-O d6 7. Nbd2) 5. c3 g6 6. d4 { Unpinning the knight } 6... Bd7 7. Nbd2 Bg7 8. dxe5 { White gives up his center. } (8. O-O O-O 9. Bd3) 8... Nxe5 9. Nxe5 dxe5 (9... Bxb5 10. Nxf7 Kxf7 11. Qb3+) 10. Qe2 O-O (10... c6 11. Bc4 O-O 12. O-O) 11. Bd3 Qe7 (11... Nh5 12. Nf3 Nf4 13. Bxf4 exf4) 12. f3 Bc6 { Stronger is } (12... Be6) 13. Nb3 { Weak, stronger is: } (13. Nc4 Rad8?! (13... a5) 14. Na5) 13... a5 14. Be3 Nd7 15. h4 a4 16. Nd2 h6 { This allows white to create some weaknesses around the black king, especially the f5 square } (16... Nc5 17. Bc2 Ne6 18. h5 Nf4 19. Qf2 Nxh5) (16... h5 17. g4 Nf6 18. O-O-O Bd7) 17. h5 g5 18. Nf1 Nc5 19. Bc2 { More active is } (19. Bc4) 19... Rfd8 20. Ng3 Bd7 { Defending f5 but allowing white to castle } 21. O-O-O c6 { Controlling b5, black missed the best move: } (21... a3) 22. Rd2 { White wants to double the rooks } (22. Kb1 { Is a good silent alternative, if } 22... Be6 23. Rxd8+ Rxd8 24. Rd1 Rxd1+ 25. Qxd1 { White will play Nf5 and claim a solid advantage }) 22... Be6 23. Nf5 Bxf5 24. exf5 Rxd2 25. Qxd2 Nd7 (25... e4! { Unleashing the bishop } 26. fxe4?? (26. Rd1 exf3 27. gxf3 a3 28. b4 { Unclear position }) 26... a3 { Blacks attack is strong }) (25... Rd8?? 26. Bxc5) 26. g4 Nf6 { Black wants to play e4 whitout a pawn sac } 27. Be4 Rd8 28. Qc2 Nd5 { Both are alternatives } (28... b5) (28... a3) 29. Bf2 b5 30. a3 { A strong defensive move } 30... Bf8 31. Rd1 Qb7 32. c4 (32. Qe2) 32... bxc4 { Black can also protect the knight with } (32... Rc8 33. Kb1 (33. cxd5?? cxd5) 33... b4) 33. Qxc4 Rb8 34. Rd2 (34. Qxc6 Rc8) 34... Nb6 35. Qc3 Nd5 36. Qc4 Nb6 37. Qd3 Be7 38. Rc2 Nd5 39. Qc4 { Blacks attack has fizzled out and white will simply take the queenside pawns } 39... Bxa3 { A desperate move and an unsound sacrifice } 40. bxa3 Qb1+ 41. Kd2 Rd8 42. Bxd5 { The best move } 42... Rxd5+ 43. Ke3 Rb5 (43... Qd1 { White can't move his queen and rook } 44. Ke4 { But black has no way to exploit this }) 44. Qxc6 Rb3+ 45. Ke2 Kh7 46. f6 Rb2 47. Rxb2 Qxb2+ 48. Kf1 Qxa3 49. Qe8 { 1-0 Black resigns. } { White will play Qf8 followed by Qh7# } 1-0


[Event "Steinitz - Zukertort World Championship Match"]
