1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nf6 4. d3 d6 5. c3 g6 6. d4 Bd7 { Unpinning the knight } 7. Nbd2 Bg7 8. dxe5 Nxe5 9. Nxe5 dxe5 10. Qe2 O-O { Stillt following game 16 } 11. f3 a5 (11... Nh5 12. g3 { Defending f4 } 12... f5 13. Bc4+ Kh8 14. exf5 gxf5) 12. Bd3 (12. a4 { So that aferter 12. ... c6 13.Bd3 black can't play 13. ... b5 } 12... c6 13. Bd3) 12... Qe7 13. Nf1 Be6 14. g4?! (14. Ne3 Rfd8 15. Bc4 Bxc4 16. Nxc4 b5 17. Ne3 c6) 14... Rfd8 15. h4 Qd7 16. Bc2 h5 { The best move, otherwise white would play: } (16... b5 17. h5 c5 18. hxg6 fxg6 19. Qh2) 17. g5 (17. gxh5 Nxh5 { Black is better }) 17... Ne8 18. Ne3 Qc6 { Black should just advance on the queenside } (18... a4 19. O-O b5) 19. c4 Nd6 (19... Rd4 20. b3 b5) 20. Bd3 Rab8 { Preparing b5 } 21. Nd5 { a4 is also reasonable, controlling b5 } (21. a4) 21... Bxd5 { A mistake, allowing white to controll the center } (21... Qd7 22. O-O b5 23. b3 c6) 22. cxd5 Qd7 23. Bd2 Ra8 (23... b6? 24. Rc1 { And the c-pawn is a permanent weakness }) 24. Rc1 c6 25. Rc5 (25. dxc6 bxc6) 25... cxd5 { A mistake } (25... a4 { Defending the a-pawn } 26. O-O Ne8 27. Rfc1) 26. Rxd5 Qa4 27. a3 b6 28. Bc3 Qe8 29. Qf2 { Atacking b6 } 29... Nc8 (29... Qc6 30. O-O Nb7 31. Bb5 Qc7 32. Rfd1) 30. Bb5 Qe7 31. Rxd8+ Qxd8 32. O-O Na7 33. Bc4 (33. Ba6 { Black can't play Rc8 } 33... Qc7 34. f4 Re8 35. f5) 33... Nc6 { Much better is: } (33... Rc8 34. Ba6 (34. b3 Nb5) 34... Rc5 35. f4 exf4 36. Qxf4 Qd7) 34. Bd5 Rc8 35. f4! Qd7 (35... exf4 36. Qxf4 { Zukertort can't defend f7 }) 36. f5 Ne7 (36... gxf5 37. Qxf5 Qxf5 38. exf5 Nd4 39. Bxd4 exd4 40. f6 Bf8 41. g6 { White wins }) 37. Ba2 gxf5 (37... Bh8 { This avoids the fork after f6, but allows a cute mate } 38. Bxf7+ Kxf7 39. fxg6+ Ke6 40. Qf6+ Bxf6 41. Rxf6#) 38. exf5 Bf8 39. Qf3 (39. Qxb6?? Nd5) 39... e4 40. Qxh5 { 1-0 Black resigns. } { Mate is inevitable } 1-0


