1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. Bg5 Be7 5. Nf3 O-O 6. c5 { Weak, the simple e3 is much better } (6. e3 h6 7. Bh4 b6 8. Bd3 Bb7 9. O-O Nbd7 10. Qe2 c5 11. Bg3 Ne4 12. cxd5 exd5) 6... b6 { The obvious move, this attacks the c-pawn and allows Steinitz to develop the queens bishop } 7. b4 bxc5 (7... a5 8. a3 Ne4 9. Bxe7 Qxe7 10. Rc1 axb4 11. axb4) 8. dxc5 { Surely bxc5 is better } (8. bxc5 Ne4 9. Bxe7 Qxe7 10. Qc2 Nxc3 11. Qxc3 Ba6 { White is fine }) 8... a5 9. a3 d4 { A great move, white can't take the pawn } 10. Bxf6 (10. Nxd4 axb4) (10. Qxd4 Qxd4 11. Nxd4 axb4) 10... gxf6 { Otherwise Ne4 would gain a tempo. Black's king is completly safe } (10... Bxf6 11. Ne4 Be7) 11. Na4 (11. Ne4 Qd5 12. Qxd4 Qxd4 13. Nxd4 axb4) 11... e5 (11... axb4 12. axb4 Nc6 13. b5 Na5 { White can't take the d-pawn } 14. Nxd4 (14. Qxd4 Qxd4 15. Nxd4 e5 16. Nc2 Nb3) 14... e5 15. Nc2 Nb3 16. Qxd8 Rxd8 17. Ra3 (17. Rb1 Bf5 18. Rxb3 Bxc2 19. Rb2 Rd1#) 17... Be6 { Black is dominating the game }) 12. b5 Be6 13. g3 (13. c6 { Seems better: } 13... Nxc6 (13... Qd5 14. e3 dxe3 15. Qxd5 exf2+ 16. Kxf2 Bxd5) 14. bxc6 Rb8 { Threat is Bb3 winning the knight. } 15. Qc1 e4 16. Nd2 { The massive center is enough compensation }) 13... c6 14. bxc6? { This just helps black to develop his knight } (14. b6 Na6 15. Rc1 Qd5) 14... Nxc6 15. Bg2 Rb8 { The threat is Bb3 } 16. Qc1 d3 17. e3 { White can't take the pawn since the king would be stuck in the center after: } (17. exd3 Qxd3) 17... e4 18. Nd2 f5 { Steinitz's enjoys a tremendous advantage in the center } 19. O-O Re8 { Defending the e-pawn against possible attacks with g4 or f3 } 20. f3 { White has to break down blacks center } (20. g4 Bf6 21. Rb1 Be5 22. gxf5 Bxf5 23. Rxb8 Bxb8 24. Nb6 Qh4) 20... Nd4 { A knight sacrifice and the e- and d-pawn become unstoppable } 21. exd4 (21. Kh1 Nc2 22. fxe4 Bf6 23. Rb1 Rxb1 24. Qxb1 Nxe3 25. Re1 Nxg2 26. Kxg2 fxe4) 21... Qxd4+ 22. Kh1 e3 { Steinitz does not care about the knight on a4 } 23. Nc3 Bf6 24. Ndb1 { Setting up for the next game } 24... d2 25. Qc2 (25. Nxd2 exd2 26. Qc2 Qxc3 27. Qxc3 Bxc3 { Black wins }) 25... Bb3 26. Qxf5 d1=Q 27. Nxd1 Bxd1 28. Nc3 e2 (28... Qxc3 29. Rfxd1 e2 30. Re1 Qxa1 31. Rxa1 Bxa1) 29. Raxd1 Qxc3 { 0-1 White resigns. } 0-1


