{ One natural tendency for such position is that all pieces will gravitate towards kingside, as it is much easier for king to 0-0 than 0-0-0 since there are 5 pieces in the way for 0-0-0 while only queen needs to move for 0-0. As both sides castle to same side, this starting position usually result in fairly balanced games. } { [%cal Gb1c3,Gc1b3,Gd2d3,Ge2e4,Ge1d2,Gf2f4,Gg2g3,Gf1g2] }
1. e4 { [%cal Gd2d3,Gb1c3] } (1. d4 { [%cal Ge2e3,Gb1c3] } 1... d5) (1. c4 { an alternative set up goal could be like this like in Edouard - Radoslaw game. } { [%csl Gc3,Gc4][%cal Gb1c3,Ge2e3,Gc1e2,Gf2f4,Gd1c2] }) 1... e5 { both e4 e5 and d4 d5 are logical. } *


