] } 42. dxc5 { [%clk 0:00:33] } 42... Bc7 { [%csl Gb6,Gd6,Ga6] [%clk 0:00:13] } 43. b4 { has to be taken, otherwise b5 in the future or even b5 cb c6 Nc5. } { [%cal Gc3b3,Gb4b5] [%clk 0:00:30] } 43... axb4 44. Nxb4+ { [%clk 0:00:34] } 44... Kb7 { [%clk 0:00:10] } 45. Rb3 { [%csl Gb7,Gf6][%cal Gb4d5] [%clk 0:00:36] } 45... Ka8 46. Nxc6 { white converted his positional advantage into material one. } { [%csl Gc5,Ga4] [%clk 0:00:37] } 46... Rc8 { [%clk 0:00:14] } 47. Nb4 { [%clk 0:00:23] } 47... e5 { [%clk 0:00:11] } 48. Rd3 { [%clk 0:00:23] } 48... Ba5 { clumsy pieces. } { [%csl Gd7,Gf8,Gc8,Ga8,Gb6][%cal Gb4d5] [%clk 0:00:13] } 49. Rxd7 { too early to simplify maybe? without exchange on d7, knight was sitting on f8 and black pieces lacked harmony. } { [%clk 0:00:26] } 49... Nxd7 { [%clk 0:00:17] } 50. Nd3 { now black has a target. } { [%csl Gc5,Gd7,Gc8] [%clk 0:00:30] } 50... Nb6 { [%clk 0:00:19] } 51. Re4 { [%clk 0:00:28] } 51... Kb7 { [%clk 0:00:19] } 52. Nb2 { [%clk 0:00:27] } 52... Nd5 { [%clk 0:00:19] } 53. Nc4 { [%clk 0:00:29] } 53... Bc7 { [%clk 0:00:23] } 54. Re1 { [%clk 0:00:29] } 54... Nb4+ { [%clk 0:00:19] } 55. Kc3 { [%clk 0:00:31] } 55... Nd5+ { [%clk 0:00:21] } 56. Kc2 { [%clk 0:00:34] } 56... Nb4+ { [%clk 0:00:25] } 57. Kc3 { [%clk 0:00:35] } 57... Nd5+ { [%clk 0:00:29] } 58. Kd3 { [%clk 0:00:39] } 58... Kc6 { [%clk 0:00:29] } 59. Ra1 { [%clk 0:00:36] } 59... Rb8 { [%clk 0:00:31] } 60. Ra3 { [%clk 0:00:14] } 60... Rb4 { [%clk 0:00:32] } 61. a5 Nf4+ { [%clk 0:00:26] } 62. Kc3 { black managed to stabilize and gain activity in the time trouble. compare pieces to after move 49. } { [%csl Gf4,Gc7,Gb4,Gc6] [%clk 0:00:13] } 62... Nd5+ { [%clk 0:00:25] } 63. Kd3 { [%clk 0:00:17] } 63... Nf4+ { so the story of the game: things have developed around b pawn, white tied blacks pieces there. stabilised in the center. then slowly expanded on kingside and gained space. then switched back to queenside for a breakthrough and converted into a material advantage, but unfor