w has potential f4 and get his pieces into game: because if knight is taken on f5, after exf5, the diagonal for h1 bishop will start to get open. will be followed by g3 at some point. Whereas, with dxe5 black could keep whites knight on f3 and bishop on h1 would take long time to get into game as well as bishop on g3. } { [%csl Gf5,Gc6] [%clk 0:06:21] } 14... O-O-O { [%csl Gd8,Gd2] [%clk 0:03:57] } 15. Qe2 { [%csl Gh5,Gc4] [%clk 0:06:05] } 15... g4 { [%csl Gf4] [%clk 0:03:14] } (15... Bd7 16. Qxh5 (16. Nf5) 16... Bg4 { [%csl Gg4,Gh5,Gd1] }) 16. Bf4 { [%clk 0:05:10] } 16... Bg7 { whites pieces are getting squares now. first d4, then f4. } { [%cal Gg2g3,Gd4f5] [%clk 0:02:48] } 17. Nf5 { [%clk 0:04:07] } 17... Bd7 { [%clk 0:02:16] } 18. g3 { [%clk 0:03:44] } 18... Bxf5 { [%clk 0:01:43] } 19. exf5 { white has solved his main issues, while black made no progress, but has to deal with e6 square and other issues. } { [%csl Gf4,Gh1,Gg7,Ge6,Gd5] [%clk 0:03:47] } 19... c6 { [%clk 0:01:47] } 20. Qe3 { [%csl Ga7] [%clk 0:03:06] } 20... Kb8 { [%clk 0:01:45] } 21. Rd4 { [%csl Ga4][%cal Gd4a4] [%clk 0:03:09] } 21... d5 { [%clk 0:01:02] } 22. Rfd1 { white suddenly started a queenside attack. } { [%cal Gf4b8,Gh1a8,Gd4a4] [%clk 0:01:23] } 22... Bf8 { [%clk 0:00:26] } 23. Ra4 { [%clk 0:01:01] } 23... b6 { [%clk 0:00:22] } 24. Qe2 { white has forced black to some pawn pushes and weaken his queenside. } { [%csl Ga6] [%clk 0:00:56] } 24... b5 { a desparate move in time trouble which allows white some tactics. } { [%clk 0:00:10] } 25. Nxb5 { [%clk 0:00:36] } 25... cxb5 { [%clk 0:00:14] } 26. Ra5 { [%clk 0:00:40] } 26... a6 27. Rxa6 { [%clk 0:00:43] } 27... Rd6 { [%csl Gh1,Gf4] } 28. Ra5 { [%clk 0:00:35] } 28... Nd8 29. Rxb5+ { white not only got 3 pawns for knight, but king is completely open. bishops got diagonals and d5 will also fall. black is completely busted now. } { [%clk 0:00:14] } 29... Nb7 { [%clk 0:00:11] } 30. Rdxd5 { [%clk 0:00:11] } 30... Rg7 { what a turnaround for bishop. never moved from h1 since the beginning but has got so much power now. } { [%cal Gh1a8] [%clk 0:00:11] } 31. Rxe5 fxe5 { [%clk 0:00:14] } 32. Qxe5 { [%clk 0:00:11] } 32... Qd8 33. a4 Rc7 34. Kb1?? (34. Bd5 { white panicked in time trouble and blundered bishop. He could block d file with Bd5 and followed with c4. } { [%csl Gc4,Gd6,Gc7,Gd8][%cal Gc2c4] }) 34... Rd1+ { [%cal Gd1h1] [%clk 0:00:11] } 35. Ka2 { [%clk 0:00:12] } 35... Rxh1 { [%clk 0:00:14] } 36. Qe4 { [%csl Gc7][%cal Gf4c7,Ge4h1] [%clk 0:00:10] } 36... Bd6 { [%clk 0:00:11] } 37. Bxd6 Qxd6 { [%clk 0:00:11] } 38. Qxh1 { [%clk 0:00:11] } 38... Qd4 { black is looking for perpetual now. } { [%csl Ga4,Gc2][%cal Gb2b3,Gc7c2] } 39. Ka3 Qd6+ { [%clk 0:00:10] } 40. Ka2 { [%clk 0:00:10] } 40... Qd4 { [%clk 0:00:11] } 41. Ka3 { [%clk 0:00:12] } 41... Qd6+ { [%clk 0:00:11] } (41... Qxf2 { is a hard move to make with 10 seconds. black wanted to get repetition instead. Objectively Qxf2 could be good but practically it is hard decision to take without being sure not to blunder anything. } { [%csl Gg3][%cal Gf2g3] }) 42. Rb4 { white declined repetition. rightly so. } { [%clk 0:00:13] } 42... Ka7 43. Qe4 { [%clk 0:00:16] } 43... Na5 44. Qd4+ Qxd4 { [%clk 0:00:10] } 45. Rxd4 { [%clk 0:00:12] } 45... Rxc2 { [%clk 0:00:10] } 46. Rf4 { [%csl Gf8][%cal Gf5f8] [%clk 0:00:11] } 46... Rc4 47. f6 (47. Rxc4 Nxc4+ 48. Kb4 Nxb2 49. f6 Nd3+ 50. Kc4 Ne5+ 51. Kd5 Ng6 { knight alone cannot deal with king and pawn, while a pawn keeps blacks king away. } { [%csl Ga7,Ga4][%cal Gd5e6,Gf6f7,Ge6f6] }) 47... Rc8 { [%clk 0:00:10] } 48. f7 { [%clk 0:00:12] } 48... Rf8 { [%clk 0:00:12] } 49. b4 { [%clk 0:00:12] } 49... Nc6 { [%clk 0:00:15] } 50. Rf5 { too many pawns and blacks position is not holdable anymore. } { [%clk 0:00:11] } 50... Nd4 { [%clk 0:00:18] } 51. Rf6 { [%clk 0:00:13] } 51... Kb7 { [%clk 0:00:11] } 52. b5 { [%clk 0:00:16] } 52... Kc7 { [%clk 0:00:15] } 53. Kb4 { [%clk 0:00:18] } 53... Kd7 { [%clk 0:00:19] } 54. b6 { [%clk 0:00:15] } 